The paper deals with a communication system involving caching, erasure coding, and state feedback, which are all topics typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of decentralized cache placement, which falls under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a delivery scheme based on a previous work by Gatzianas et al., which could be considered as a form of machine learning or data mining, falling under the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the benefits of the proposed scheme, which could be considered as a form of performance evaluation or experimental design, falling under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
